</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,1440,722,984]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,363,722,748]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[374,417,723,749]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Size</emphasis>
. Length 
<quantity box="[524,616,722,749]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity box="[707,800,723,749]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[814,873,723,748]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[964,1047,722,749]" captionStart="Figures 98–101" captionStartId="65.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-10@65.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="Figures 98–101. Habitus of Axina species. 98) Axina lateralis. 99) A. luzia. 100) A. munda. 101) A. minas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565023" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565023/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[1060,1121,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium dark castaneous; antenna testaceous; prothorax bicolorous, venter, lower sides of pronotum, pterothorax, and legs black, pronotal disc castaneous; elytra bicolorous, mostly testaceous, epipleural margin and region in front of apex brown. 
<emphasis box="[1375,1434,790,816]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons about as wide as length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 45/8. 
<emphasis box="[1232,1310,823,849]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/PL 95/125; elytra, asetiferous punctures scattered, punctures extend posteriorly to elytral 3/4, interstitial spaces very wide; EL/EW 410/60. 
<emphasis box="[1211,1317,890,916]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[200,279,924,951]" captionStart="Figures 50–55" captionStartId="51.[192,279,978,1004]" captionTargetBox="[320,1271,213,948]" captionTargetId="figure-10@51.[320,1271,213,948]" captionText="Figures 50–55. Aedeagi. 5) Axina basalis. 51) A. lateralis. 52) A. munda. 53) A. phallospina. 54) A. proxima. 55) A. trinalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4586063/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
), phallobasic lobes short, flattened laterally; phallic plates serrate near phallic apex; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,1440,999,1059]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,310,999,1025]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Variation.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[316,359,1000,1026]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Size</emphasis>
. Length 9.5–13.0 mm; width 2.2–3.0 mm. Except for body size, the available specimens are quite homogeneous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,1440,1074,1135]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,376,1074,1101]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[701,779,1074,1100]" name="Bolivia" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
during October, in a transitional forest at 
<quantity box="[1248,1376,1074,1101]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" unit="m" value="375.0" valueMax="400.0" valueMin="350.0">
350– 
<specimenCount box="[1302,1376,1074,1101]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="generic">400 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Others were collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[458,523,1108,1134]" name="Brazil" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
from November and December, at altitudes that range from 
<quantity box="[1200,1327,1108,1135]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" unit="m" value="400.0" valueMax="500.0" valueMin="300.0">
300– 
<specimenCount box="[1254,1327,1108,1135]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="generic">500 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
